'''Ferdinand Essandja''' (sometimes '''Fernand Essendja''' or '''Ferdinand Esandja''') was a Congolese politician and businessman. He was the chairman of the ''[[Parti de l’Unité Congolaise]]'' in 1959.<ref>{{cite journal| author-link =| title = Le Congrès de Coquilhatville et la création du parti national du progrès (P.N.P.)| journal = Courrier hebdomadaire du CRISP| issue = 41| pages = 1–5| publisher = CRISP| date = 1959| language = French| url = https://www.cairn.info/revue-courrier-hebdomadaire-du-crisp-1959-41-page-1.htm| doi = 10.3917/cris.041.0001}}</ref> He attended the [[Belgo-Congolese Round Table Conference]] in early 1960 as a delegate of the ''[[Parti National du Progrès]]'' (PNP) to participate in negotiations for the [[Belgian Congo]]'s independence.<ref>{{cite book| title = The Belgo-Congolese Round Table: The historic days of February 1960| date = 1960| location = Brussels| url = https://archive.org/details/TheBelgo-congoleseRoundTable| page= 62}}</ref> At one point he served as the mayor of the [[Barumbu]] commune of [[Léopoldville]]. In June 1961 Essendja became the managing director of [[Air Zaïre#Air Congo|Air Congo]], the [[flag carrier]] of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].<ref>{{cite book| last= Artigue |first= Pierre |title = Qui sont les leaders congolais?| publisher = Éditions Europe-Afrique| volume = 3| date = 1961| pages = 76| language = French| url = https://books.google.com/books?id=24c5AQAAIAAJ&dq=}}</ref> By 1967 he was the vice president of company.<ref>{{cite magazine| date = 13 April 1967| page = [https://www.flightglobal.com/FlightPDFArchive/1967/1967%20-%200568.PDF 544]| title = Air Congo| magazine = [[Flight International]]}}</ref>

